      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1816_05_20_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <date when="1816-05-20"/>May 20, 1816</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Persongraphy.xml#MileX1">
                     My dear M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles<lb/>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I should be much<lb/>
               obliged to you if you<lb/>
               could buy for me a<lb/>
               yard &amp; half of thin <hi rend="underline">fine</hi><lb/>
               clear<del>muslin</del> India<lb/>
               muslin for morning<lb/>
               handkerchiefs &amp; borders<lb/></p>
            <p>- I should wish to have<lb/>
               it finer and <hi rend="underline">clearer</hi><lb/>
               than the last you were<lb/>
               so good to get for me<lb/>
               &amp; I should not think<lb/>
               15 or 16 shillings too high<lb/>
               a price for what would<lb/>
               be really good - There<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1816_05_20_page02.jpg"/>
               is a kind of muslin which<lb/>
               is not so thick as Jaconette<lb/>
               nor so thin as buck<lb/>
               muslin I believe it<lb/>
               is called <hi rend="underline">Mull</hi> &amp; this<lb/>
               is the kind I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. prefer<lb/></p>
            <p> I am not in any<lb/>
               hurry therefore pray<lb/>
               do not inconvenience<lb/>
               yourself as to <hi rend="underline">time</hi><lb/></p>
            <p> Whenever you have<lb/>
               bought it send it over<lb/>
               as you did <del>befo</del> the last<lb/>
               between the leaves of any<lb/>
               book or pamphlet.<lb/>
               Which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Mile2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> may<lb/>
               recommend &amp; direct<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1816_05_20_page03.jpg"/>
               - <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeM1">1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. cover to Miss E.</persName><lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography#FoxC1">2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> cover to CJ Fox Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></persName><lb/>
               3 cover to <persName ref="./Personography#TaylW1">W Taylor Esq</persName><lb/>
               <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7901000">Castle Dublin</placeName><lb/></p>
            <p> I hope you will be<lb/>
               able to send me a<lb/>
               good account of<lb/>
               your own &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Mile2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles's</persName><lb/>
               health - I have the<lb/>
               pleasure to tell you<lb/>
               that my father's is<lb/>
               wonderfully recovered<lb/>
               - within this last month<lb/>
               - <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeR1">He</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. E</persName> are in<lb/>
               <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/7001306">Dublin</placeName> &amp; will be there<lb/>
               a few days - my <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeR1">father</persName><lb/>
               is still trying <unclear>Ercpti</unclear>on<lb/>
               wheel carriages - I wish<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Mile2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></persName>. Miles would sometimes<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1816_05_20_page04.jpg"/>
               write to me - I always like<lb/>
               to hear from him <lb/></p>
            <p> I enclose a<add><hi rend="underline">note</hi></add> <del>draft</del> on Hoare<lb/>
               to him for £5 - with this I beg<lb/>
               you to pay for the muslin<lb/>
               <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1816_05_20_page01.jpg"/>
               and<lb/>
               to pay<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography#HuntX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi><lb/>
                  Hunter</persName><lb/>
               for any<lb/>
               muslin<lb/>
               &amp; lace<lb/>
               he may<lb/>
               have<lb/>
               paid<lb/>
               you<lb/>
               for<lb/>
               that no<lb/>
               such<lb/>
               articles<lb/>
               may<lb/>
               appear<lb/>
               in his<lb/>
               accounts<lb/>
               against<lb/>   
               <unclear>M</unclear></p>
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personagraphy.xml#EdgeM1">ME</persName>
               20 May 1816   
            </closer>
            <postscript>
